{"questionId":"1249326","questionHtml":"<p>A fuel has mass density <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ρ</mi></math> and energy density <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>u</mi></math>. What mass of the fuel has to be burned to&nbsp;release thermal energy <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>E</mi></math>?</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>A.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>ρ</mi><mi>E</mi></mrow><mi>u</mi></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>B.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>u</mi><mi>E</mi></mrow><mi>ρ</mi></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>C.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi>ρ</mi><mi>u</mi></mrow><mi>E</mi></mfrac></math></p>\n<p>D.&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ρ</mi><mi>u</mi><mi>E</mi></math></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A</p>","meta":{"questionId":"1249326","referenceCode":"21N.1A.SL.TZ0.28","subjectId":"59-dp-physics-first-assessment-2025","title":"A fuel has mass density ρ and energy density u. What mass of the fuel has to be burned to release thermal energy E? A. ρEu B. uEρ C. ρuE D. ρuE","paper":"1A","level":"SL","questionNumber":"28","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["A. Space, time and motion","A.3 Work, energy and power"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}